'''契约论'''（{{lang-en|contractarianism<ref name="陈德中2015">{{cite book|author=陈德中|title=政治现实主义的逻辑：“自主性”与“封闭性”缘与由: "自主性"与"封闭性"缘与由|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=kodVDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT149|date=1 January 2015|publisher=|isbn=978-7-5161-5894-4|pages=149–|access-date=2019-01-02|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021065532/https://books.google.com/books?id=kodVDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT149}}</ref>}}），又作'''契约主义'''，<ref name="曾瑞明2014">{{cite book|author=曾瑞明|title=參與對等與全球正義|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ueSbAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA82|date=30 April 2014|publisher=聯經出版事業公司|isbn=978-957-08-4382-8|pages=82–|access-date=2019-01-02|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021065538/https://books.google.com/books?id=ueSbAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA82}}</ref>是一种对[[政治权力|政治权力]][[合法性|合法性]]的一种系统论证的政治哲学理论，<ref name="蔡拓1987">{{cite book|author=蔡拓|title=契约论研究|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=E7o0AAAAMAAJ|year=1987|publisher=南开大学出版社|access-date=2019-01-02|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021065542/https://books.google.com/books?id=E7o0AAAAMAAJ}}</ref>其最基本的论点是国家的产生来自人与人之间或人民与统治者之间相互订立的契约。<ref>"For the name social contract (or original contract) often covers two different kinds of contract, and, in tracing the evolution of the theory, it is well to distinguish them. Both were current in the 17th century and both can be discovered in Greek political thought. ... [The first] generally involved some theory of the origin of the state. The second form of social contract may be more accurately called the contract of government, or the contract of submission....  Generally, it has nothing to do with the origins of society, but, presupposing a society already formed, it purports to define the terms on which that society is to be governed: the people have made a contract with their ruler which determines their relations with him. They promise him obedience, while he promises his protection and good government. While he keeps his part of the bargain, they must keep theirs, but if he misgoverns the contract is broken and allegiance is at an end." [[J._W._Gough|J. W. Gough]], ''The Social Contract'' (Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1936), pp.{{nbsp}}2–3. Modern revivals of social contract theories have not been as concerned with the origin of the state.</ref>

==概念渊源==
契约论最早源自于[[古希腊|古希腊]][[智者学派|智者学派]]，它描绘了一幅法律诞生之前的自然状态，为了走出自然状态进入文明社会，国家和法律就诞生了，统治的合法性建立在个体的同意和授权之上，政府的权力来源于自然权利的让渡。然而，对于契约的作用，智者派学者们观点各异甚至对立，[[普罗泰戈拉|普罗泰戈拉]]倾向于肯定契约的作用，[[安提丰|安提丰]]等则对契约及其产物——[[人为法|人为法]]基本上采取否定的态度。他们对社会契约形成的论证不充分，并且对其作用的表述也不够明确。

苏格拉底是欧洲政治思想史上最早提出国家与公民之间的关系是契约关系的先驱之一，即使被民众无故判处死刑，朋友劝其越狱以自保，他却为维护法律契约的权威而甘愿赴死。但是，古希腊哲学家[[伊壁鸠鲁|伊壁鸠鲁]]及其弟子亦即伊壁鸠鲁学派则是历史上最早从理论上深刻而系统地阐述了契约论思想。

伊壁鸠鲁借用和改造了[[德谟克利特|德谟克利特]]的“[[原子|原子]]”理论，认为[[国家|国家]]与[[法律|法律]]是[[契约|契约]]的产物，其价值在于保障个人的自由和安全。<ref name="蔡磊蔡昌2015">{{cite book|author1=蔡磊|author2=蔡昌|title=构建税收诚信：基于电子商务行业发展视角|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Lh2ADwAAQBAJ&pg=PT50|date=15 July 2015|publisher=|isbn=978-7-5095-6287-1|pages=50–|access-date=2019-01-02|archive-date=2020-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021065548/https://books.google.com/books?id=Lh2ADwAAQBAJ&pg=PT50}}</ref>[[伊壁鸠鲁学派|伊壁鸠鲁学派]]和[[斯多葛派|斯多葛派]]分别从人的特殊性和普遍性两个方面提出并论证了契约论。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://theory.people.com.cn/BIG5/49157/49163/3805048.html|title=古希臘羅馬時期的"契約論"|date=2005年10月27日|publisher=人民網|access-date=2019年1月2日|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102193354/http://theory.people.com.cn/BIG5/49157/49163/3805048.html|archive-date=2019年1月2日|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

